 nodes in the subtree of the `i^(th)` node which have the same label as node `i`.\n\nA subtree of a tree `T` is the tree consisting of a node in `T` and all of its descendant nodes.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/jpeg","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1519-number-of-nodes-in-the-sub-tree-with-the-same-label/1519-q3e1.jpg","sequence":1,"sha256":"39afe4235747bac1f7d9edee159f5d74311fd25074884d89d8ba9a4eeab87378","type":"image"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Input: n = 7, edges = [[0,1],[0,2],[1,4],[1,5],[2,3],[2,6]], labels = \"abaedcd\"\nOutput: [2,1,1,1,1,1,1]\nExplanation: Node 0 has label 'a' and its sub-tree has node 2 with label 'a' as well, thus the answer is 2. Notice that any node is part of its sub-tree.\nNode 1 has a label 'b'. The sub-tree of node 1 contains nodes 1,4 and 5, as nodes 4 and 5 have different labels than node 1, the answer is just 1 (the node itself).","type":"code"},{"sequence":3,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/jpeg","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1519-number-of-nodes-in-the-sub-tree-with-the-same-label/1519-q3e2.jpg","sequence":4,"sha256":"eaf6f4fcea0cddc641278048af17a9c08e90d4e376720acc9aef8265051cc679","type":"image"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: n = 4, edges = [[0,1],[1,2],[0,3]], labels = \"bbbb\"\nOutput: [4,2,1,1]\nExplanation: The sub-tree of node 2 contains only node 2, so the answer is 1.\nThe sub-tree of node 3 contains only node 3, so the answer is 1.\nThe sub-tree of node 1 contains nodes 1 and 2, both have label 'b', thus the answer is 2.\nThe sub-tree of node 0 contains nodes 0, 1, 2 and 3, all with label 'b', thus the answer is 4.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/jpeg","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1519-number-of-nodes-in-the-sub-tree-with-the-same-label/1519-q3e3.jpg","sequence":7,"sha256":"0efeec2a8b8144f5596226549c6b2fa258