--------------+\n| trans_id   | paid_by    | paid_to    | amount   | transacted_on |\n+------------+------------+------------+----------+---------------+\n| 1          | 1          | 3          | 400      | 2020-08-01    |\n| 2          | 3          | 2          | 500      | 2020-08-02    |\n| 3          | 2          | 1          | 200      | 2020-08-03    |\n+------------+------------+------------+----------+---------------+\nOutput: \n+------------+------------+------------+-----------------------+\n| user_id    | user_name  | credit     | credit_limit_breached |\n+------------+------------+------------+-----------------------+\n| 1          | Moustafa   | -100       | Yes                   | \n| 2          | Jonathan   | 500        | No                    |\n| 3          | Winston    | 9900       | No                    |\n| 4          | Luis       | 800        | No                    |\n+------------+------------+------------+-----------------------+\nExplanation: \nMoustafa paid $400 on \"2020-08-01\" and received $200 on \"2020-08-03\", credit (100 -400 +200) = -$100\nJonathan received $500 on \"2020-08-02\" and paid $200 on \"2020-08-08\", credit (200 +500 -200) = $500\nWinston received $400 on \"2020-08-01\" and paid $500 on \"2020-08-03\", credit (10000 +400 -500) = $9990\nLuis did not received any transfer, credit = $800","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/bank-account-summary/","problemName":"Bank Account Summary","problemNumber":1555,"problemSlug":"bank-account-summary","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1555,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["String"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given an integer `n`, add a dot (\".\") as the thousands separator and return it in string format.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: n = 987\nOutput: \"987\"","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: n = 1234\nOutput: \"1.234\"","type":