e will not make it so. So the maximum number of edges we can remove is 2.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1579-remove-max-number-of-edges-to-keep-graph-fully-traversable/1579-ex2.png]]\n\n**\n\nInput: n = 4, edges = [[3,1,2],[3,2,3],[1,1,4],[2,1,4]]\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: Notice that removing any edge will not make the graph fully traversable by Alice and Bob.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\n**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1579-remove-max-number-of-edges-to-keep-graph-fully-traversable/1579-ex3.png]]\n\n**\n\nInput: n = 4, edges = [[3,2,3],[1,1,2],[2,3,4]]\nOutput: -1\nExplanation: In the current graph, Alice cannot reach node 4 from the other nodes. Likewise, Bob cannot reach 1. Therefore it's impossible to make the graph fully traversable.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= edges.length <= min(10⁵, 3 * n * (n - 1) / 2)`\n\n- `edges[i].length == 3`\n\n- `1 <= typei <= 3`\n\n- `1 <= ui < vi <= n`\n\n- All tuples `(typei, ui, vi)` are distinct.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-max-number-of-edges-to-keep-graph-fully-traversable/","problemName":"Remove Max Number of Edges to Keep Graph Fully Traversable","problemNumber":1579,"problemSlug":"remove-max-number-of-edges-to-keep-graph-fully-traversable","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1579,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[{"assetIndex":0,"bytes":1390,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1580-put-boxes-into-the-warehouse-ii/1580-22.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/1580-22.png","sha256":"a4bd19eaca95cb0dc414a2133dfd6e545dfc3e3172566b21159c262c36b2b384"},{"assetIndex":1,"bytes":1239,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1580-put-boxes-into-the-warehouse-ii/1580-22-1.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/1580-22-1.png","sha256":"fded6ada6ca67a7ceef391cf1eca7788512074140ceb11fa04f55428710e2a89"},{"assetIndex":2,"bytes":1418,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/