nce":4,"text":"We can store the boxes in the following order:\n1- Put the yellow box in room 2 from either the left or right side.\n2- Put the orange box in room 3 from the right side.\n3- Put the green box in room 1 from the left side.\n4- Put the red box in room 0 from the left side.\nNotice that there are other valid ways to put 4 boxes such as swapping the red and green boxes or the red and orange boxes.\n\n**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1580-put-boxes-into-the-warehouse-ii/1580-22-2.png","sequence":5,"sha256":"973ffa12f5be7d9beb592b480e34a37d6f2c3271cc972c3cbe6cdfa2826ba7c9","type":"image"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Input:** boxes = [3,5,5,2], warehouse = [2,1,3,4,5]\n**Output:** 3\n**Explanation:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1580-put-boxes-into-the-warehouse-ii/1580-22-3.png","sequence":7,"sha256":"9ff0b50cf50be430b8ca96afaad1ca1366c41f570c558756e7c823fd39c361af","type":"image"},{"sequence":8,"text":"It is not possible to put the two boxes of height 5 in the warehouse since there's only 1 room of height >= 5.\nOther valid solutions are to put the green box in room 2 or to put the orange box first in room 2 before putting the green and red boxes.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `n == warehouse.length`\n\n- `1 <= boxes.length, warehouse.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= boxes[i], warehouse[i] <= 10⁹`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Greedy","Array","Sorting"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given two arrays of positive integers, `boxes` and `warehouse`, representing the heights of some boxes of unit width and the heights of `n` rooms in a warehouse respectively. The warehouse's rooms are labeled from `0` to `n - 1` from left to right where `warehouse[i]` (0-indexed) is the height of the `i^(th)` room.\n\nBoxes are put into the warehouse by the following rules:\n\n- Boxes cannot be stacked.\n\n- You can rearrange the insertion order of the boxes.\n\n- Boxes can be pushed into the warehouse from **either side** (left or right)\n\n- If the height of some room in the warehouse is less than the height of a box, then that box and all other boxes behind it will be stopped before that room.\n\nReturn *the maximum number of boxes you can put into the warehouse.*\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1580-put-boxes-into-the-warehouse-ii/1580-22.png]]\n\n**Input:** boxes = [1,2,2,3,4], warehouse = [3,4,1,2]\n**Output:** 4\n**Explanation:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1580-put-boxes-into-the-warehouse-ii/1580-22-1.png]]\n\nWe can store the boxes in the following order:\n1- Put the yellow box in room 2 from either the left or right side.\n2- Put the orange box in room 3 from the right side.\n3- Put the green box in room 1 from the left side.\n4- Put the red box in room 0 from the left side.\nNotice that there are other valid ways to put 4 boxes such as swapping the red and green boxes or the red and orange boxes.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1580-put-boxes-into-the-warehouse-ii/1580-22-2.png]]\n\n**Input:** boxes = [3,5,5,2], warehouse = [2,1,3,4,5]\n**Output:** 3\n**Explanation:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1580-put-boxes-into-the-warehouse-ii/1580-22-3.png]]\n\nIt is not possible to put the two boxes of height 5 in the warehouse since there's only 1 room of height >= 5.\nOther valid solutions are to put the green box in room 2 or to put the orange box first in room 2 before putting the green and red boxes.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `n == warehouse.length`\n\n- `1 <= boxes.length, warehouse.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= boxes[i], warehouse[i] <= 10⁹`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/put-boxes-into-the-warehouse-ii/","problemName":"Put Boxes Into the Warehouse II","problemNumber":1580,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revi